# GitNexus enforcement

## North star

> **GitNexus is the default reasoning layer for every task â€” not a fallback when code is unfamiliar.** Prefer graph + embeddings when the index is fresh. Use `query` to orient (BM25 + vectors). Use `cypher` for precise structural graph questions. Refresh autonomously when stale or embeddings are missing. Classical tools only **after refresh fails** or GN is wrong â€” say why.

**Model tiers:** the graph + gates improve **every** agent â€” budget/local models gain the most *relative* lift; flagship models waste fewer tokens and follow the same enforced loop. Local LLM / zero API cost: rebuild context freely; do not skip gates for speed.

## Every task (not â€œunfamiliar code onlyâ€‌)

Use the graph for **all** agent work â€” explore, debug, fix, refactor, review, rename, commit â€” not only architecture questions.

| Task type | Graph role |
| --- | --- |
| Answer / explain / debug | `query` â†’ `context` â†’ `cypher` if structural â†’ Read offset/limit |
| Field / property data flow | READ schema â†’ `cypher` (`ACCESSES` read/write) |
| N-hop call chains, overrides, process steps | READ schema â†’ `cypher` |
| Statement-level data/control flow, taint | `pdg_query` / `explain` / `trace` (see deep precision) |
| Edit runtime source (any size) | `impact` upstream before Write/StrReplace |
| Refactor / rename / shared code | `impact` + `rename` dry_run OR `context` on hub symbols |
| Review / â€œwhat did I change?â€‌ | `detect_changes`; `query` to orient |
| Session start | `agent-brief` or repo context; confirm kit health |

**Anti-patterns:** reserving GitNexus for big exploratory prompts; grep/read from memory on â€œfamiliarâ€‌ files; grepping field names instead of `cypher`; **StrReplace/find-and-replace for symbol renames** instead of `rename` dry_run; skipping `impact` on â€œsmallâ€‌ edits; jumping to `context`/`impact`/`grep` without `query` first (skips embeddings). `SemanticSearch` is blocked â€” use `query`.

## Graph + embeddings + cypher (layered)

| Need | Tool | Why |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Orient â€” any fuzzy or grounding step | `query` | Hybrid BM25 + **embedding** vectors (RRF) |
| One symbol, callers, 360آ° | `context` | Structural graph (canned API) |
| **Precise structural graph questions** | **`cypher`** | Raw traversals the canned tools don't express |
| Pre-edit blast radius | `impact` | Graph traversal |
| Pre-commit / done | `detect_changes` | Diff â†’ processes |

### When to escalate to `cypher` (after `query` / `context`)

READ `gitnexus://repo/__GITNEXUS_REPO__/schema` before ad-hoc Cypher.

| Question | Cypher edge / pattern |
| --- | --- |
| Who reads/writes field/property X? | `ACCESSES` with `reason: read` / `write` |
| Custom N-hop call chain | `CALLS` variable-length path |
| Method override chain | `METHOD_OVERRIDES` |
| Ordered steps in a process | `STEP_IN_PROCESS` + `r.step` |
| All methods on a class | `HAS_METHOD` |
| Diamond / multi-inheritance | `EXTENDS` multi-path MATCH |

**Order:** `query` (orient) â†’ `context` (symbol) â†’ **`cypher`** (structural precision) â†’ `impact` (before edits). Do not start with `cypher` for fuzzy questions â€” that's what `query` + embeddings are for.

Refresh always includes `--embeddings` (`gitnexus:refresh` / `agent-refresh`). Missing embeddings = stale (same as commit behind).

## Deep precision â€” PDG, taint, trace

When `cypher` isn't enough, escalate to statement-level tools (require a PDG index â€” `gitnexus:pdg`):

| Need | Tool |
| --- | --- |
| Statement-level blast radius (control + data) | `impact` with `mode: "pdg"` |
| What predicate controls a line / why does it run? | `pdg_query` (`mode: "controls"`) |
| Where does a variable's value flow / reach? | `pdg_query` (`mode: "flows"`) |
| Source â†’ sink path between two symbols | `trace` |
| Taint review â€” injection, path traversal, XSS | `explain` |

## Full tool surface â€” reach for the right one

Know every tool and *when* it wins (single-repo; cross-repo `group_*` is out of scope for this kit). Don't stop at `query`/`context` â€” the advanced tools answer in one call what takes many manual hops.

| Tool | Reach for it when |
| --- | --- |
| `query` | Orient â€” "how does X work?", find the execution flow for a concept (BM25 + vectors). Always first for fuzzy work. |
| `context` | 360آ° on ONE symbol â€” callers, callees, categorized refs, the processes it's in. After `query`, or when the symbol is known. |
| `cypher` | Precise structural questions the canned tools don't express â€” field `ACCESSES`, N-hop `CALLS`, `METHOD_OVERRIDES`, `STEP_IN_PROCESS`. READ schema first. |
| `impact` | BEFORE editing a symbol â€” upstream blast radius + risk + affected processes. `mode: "pdg"` for statement-level (control+data) precision. |
| `trace` | "How does A reach B?" â€” shortest call/member path between two symbols in ONE call (replaces 3â€“8 manual `context` hops). |
| `pdg_query` | "What condition gates this line?" (`mode: "controls"`) / "where does this variable flow?" (`mode: "flows"`). Intra-function; needs PDG. |
| `explain` | Security review â€” taint sourceâ†’sink (command/code/sql injection, path-traversal, XSS), intra- AND inter-procedural. Needs PDG. |
| `detect_changes` | BEFORE commit / "what did my edits affect?" â€” diff â†’ affected symbols/processes/risk. `scope`: unstaged \| staged \| all \| compare. |
| `rename` | Coordinated multi-file symbol rename â€” `dry_run: true` first. Never find-and-replace identifiers. |
| `api_impact` | BEFORE changing an HTTP route handler (framework router) â€” consumers, response-shape mismatches, middleware chain, risk. |
| `route_map` | Map routes â†’ consumers + handler + middleware; find orphaned routes. (Custom router â†’ `context` on the dispatcher instead.) |
| `shape_check` | Detect API response-shape drift â€” keys a route returns vs keys consumers access (flags MISMATCH). |
| `tool_map` | Map MCP/RPC tool definitions â†’ handler files + descriptions (tool-API work, impact of a tool-contract change). |
| `check` | Structural integrity â€” detect circular File `IMPORTS` cycles (health / CI gate). |
| `list_repos` | Only when multiple repos are indexed â€” discover/disambiguate before passing `repo:` to other tools. |

Cheap resource reads (prefer before heavy tools): `READ gitnexus://repo/__GITNEXUS_REPO__/{context|schema|clusters|processes|process/<name>}`.

