## Session (autonomous Shell)

New chat: run session health ritual if injected â€” `npm run gitnexus:agent-status`, one-sentence confirm to user.

`npm run gitnexus:agent-brief` or READ `gitnexus://repo/__GITNEXUS_REPO__/context`. Stale or missing embeddings â†’ **`npm run gitnexus:agent-refresh` first** (`required_permissions: ["all"]`). Hooks **block** Grep/Read/MCP/shell until refresh succeeds; classical tools only if refresh **fails** (say why). Never ask user to analyze.

## Stale loop (mandatory)

```
stale â†’ agent-refresh (Shell, pre-approved)
  â†’ fresh â†’ query / context / cypher / impact
  â†’ still stale after refresh â†’ agent-refresh retry once if plausible
  â†’ refresh failed â†’ classical fallback OK (one sentence why)
```

Session start runs auto-refresh when stale. Do **not** grep/read â€œwhile refreshingâ€‌ â€” refresh is the next tool, not a background hint.

## Gates (do not skip â€” every task)

```
1. brief OR context â€” session start
2. query â€” orient / ground (graph + embeddings) before reasoning or edits
3. context â†’ process â€” drill into symbols
4. cypher â€” structural precision (field ACCESSES, N-hop CALLS, overrides, process steps)
5. impact upstream â€” before runtime source edits
6. rename dry_run â€” before coordinated symbol renames (not StrReplace across files)
7. detect_changes â€” before commit / done
```

HIGH/CRITICAL impact â†’ warn before proceeding.

## When fresh â€” hooks block (enforced, not advisory)

Symbol grep â†’ `context`. **Field/property grep â†’ READ schema â†’ `cypher` (`ACCESSES`).** SemanticSearch/broad Glob â†’ `query`. Large source Read â†’ `query` â†’ `context` â†’ Read offset/limit; **data-flow / model reads â†’ `cypher` first.** Symbol **StrReplace rename** â†’ `rename` dry_run.

**Hard gates (deny until satisfied, once per session):**
- **Edit runtime source** â†’ blocked until one `impact` (or `rename`) call this session. Run blast radius first; warn on HIGH/CRITICAL.
- **`git commit`** â†’ blocked until one `detect_changes` call this session. Confirm affected processes match intent.

Enforcement is **polyglot** â€” JS/TS, Python, Rust, Go, Java, and more count as source (configure `sourceExts` in `.gnkit/gitnexus-hooks.json`).

## Deep review (intel layer)

At a **milestone** â€” feature done / big-task checkpoint / shared-code refactor / pre-ship, or "audit / find real bugs / is this solid?" â€” **and** only when the work is *substantial* (multi-file or high `impact` blast-radius): run a **microscope-waves** pass â†’ load the `gitnexus-microscope` skill. Multi-lens, opinionated (not just defects), adversarially verified, iterated in waves. Skip it for small localized changes.

## Fallback

**Only after refresh fails** (or MCP down / GN wrong after `uid` retry): classical Grep/Read OK â€” one-sentence why. While stale and refresh not yet attempted/failed: **deny classical** â€” run `agent-refresh` first.

